duck: Khan (title), a title for a ruler in Turkic and Mongolian languages and also used by Persians, Punjabis, Afghans/Pashtuns for chiefs and noblemen.
khan definition: a medieval sovereign of China and ruler over the Turkish, Tatar, and Mongol tribes.
Khan (band), an English progressive rock band in the 70s
Khan River, an ephemeral river in Namibia
Khan (Cambodia), a municipal subdivision of the administrative divisions of Cambodia
Khan Noonien Singh, a character from Star Trek, mostly featured in Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan
